divs: Sighting DetailsObject sighted on 1-30-11 at approximately 5:39 AM CST It was a faint white star-like object. It appeared to be moving faster than a satellite, and much faster than an aircraft. First sighted at 90 degrees elevation, moving from west to east. Disappeared after a sighting duration of abut 40 seconds in the east at about 30 degrees elevation. It covered about 60 degrees of azimuth. Why am I seeing these things?? They must be objects that are known, just some that I am not familiar with. After 3-4 thousand hours of flight time, you would think that I would be pretty familiar with the sky and what is in it
